						               													<description>The Middle Path is a board game about everyday Muslim problems. This hilarious, Party-style game, can be played by 2 to 4 players. Play up to 8 players by adding another deck of cards (which can be purchased separately).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player will take turns drawing cards from the deck. There are Attack cards, which move you away from the Middle Path, unless you have the correct defend card. Kind Deed cards will take you to the center of the board, unless and opponent &amp;lsquo;steals&amp;rsquo; or &amp;lsquo;obstructs&amp;rsquo; your kind deeds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although a fun party game, there is some strategy to it. Each card in the game simulates real-life problems that Muslims face on a daily basis.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 2 ways to win: First to reach the middle path or Last-Muslim-standing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 Deck = up to 4 players&amp;#10;2 Decks = up to 8 players&amp;#10;3 Decks = Sectarian violence&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
